definition.value: Catalysis of the transmembrane transfer of a calcium ion by a channel that opens in response to a mechanical stress in the form of stretching.
Catalysis of the transmembrane transfer of an ion by a channel that opens when a specific ligand has been bound by the channel complex or one of its constituent parts.
An ionotropic glutamate receptor activity that exhibits fast gating by glutamate, acts by opening a cation channel permeable to sodium and potassium, and for which kainate is an agonist.
Catalysis of the transmembrane transfer of a calcium ion by a channel that opens when a specific ligand has been bound by the channel complex or one of its constituent parts.
A ligand-gated ion channel activity which transports calcium in response to emptying of intracellular calcium stores.
Catalysis of the transmembrane transfer of a sodium ion by a channel that opens when a specific ligand has been bound by the channel complex or one of its constituent parts.
Catalysis of the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction -  fructose(out) -eq- fructose(in).

Catalysis of the transfer of substances, sized less than 1000 Da, from one side of the membrane to the other. The transmembrane portions of porins consist exclusively of beta-strands which form a beta-barrel. They are found in the outer membranes of Gram-negative bacteria, mitochondria, plastids and possibly acid-fast Gram-positive bacteria.

Catalysis of the transfer of a solute from one side of a membrane to the other, up its concentration gradient. The transporter binds the solute and undergoes a series of conformational changes. Transport works equally well in either direction and is driven by a chemiosmotic source of energy, not direct ATP coupling. Chemiosmotic sources of energy include uniport, symport or antiport.
Catalysis of the transport of a single molecular species across a membrane -  transport is independent of the movement of any other molecular species.

Enables the active transport of a solute across a membrane by a mechanism whereby two or more species are transported together in the same direction in a tightly coupled process not directly linked to a form of energy other than chemiosmotic energy.
Catalysis of the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction -  solute(out) + cation(out) -eq- solute(in) + cation(in).
Catalysis of the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction -  solute(out) + H+(out) -eq- solute(in) + H+(in).
Catalysis of the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction -  anion(out) + cation(out) -eq- anion(in) + cation(in).

Enables the active transport of a solute across a membrane by a mechanism whereby two or more species are transported in opposite directions in a tightly coupled process not directly linked to a form of energy other than chemiosmotic energy. The reaction is -  solute A(out) + solute B(in) -eq- solute A(in) + solute B(out).
Catalysis of the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction -  solute(out) + cation(in) -eq- solute(in) + cation(out).
Catalysis of the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction -  solute(out) + H+(in) -eq- solute(in) + H+(out).
Catalysis of the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction -  anion A(out) + anion B(in) -eq- anion A(in) + anion B(out).
Catalysis of the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction -  glucose(out) -eq- glucose(in).
Catalysis of the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction -  sialate(out) + cation(out) -eq- sialate(in) + cation(in).
Catalysis of the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction -  H+(out) + drug(in) -eq- H+(in) + drug(out).
Catalysis of the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction -  H+(out) + amiloride(in) -eq- H+(in) + amiloride(out).
Catalysis of the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction -  H+(out) + cycloheximide(in) -eq- H+(in) + cycloheximide(out).
Catalysis of the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction -  H+(out) + benomyl(in) -eq- H+(in) + benomyl(out).
Catalysis of the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction -  H+(out) + monoamine(in) -eq- H+(in) + monoamine(out).
Catalysis of the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction -  H+(out) + polyamine(in) -eq- H+(in) + polyamine(out).
Catalysis of the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction -  H+(out) + fluconazole(in) -eq- H+(in) + fluconazole(out).
Catalysis of the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction -  H+(out) + aminotriazole(in) -eq- H+(in) + aminotriazole(out).

Catalysis of the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction -  organophosphate(out) + inorganic phosphate(in) -eq- organophosphate(in) + inorganic phosphate(out).
Catalysis of the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction -  phosphate(out) + H+(out) -eq- phosphate(in) + H+(in).

label.value: inorganic solute uptake transmembrane transporter activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the transfer of an inorganic solute from the outside of a cell to the inside of the cell across a membrane.
Catalysis of the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction -  Na+(out) + inorganic phosphate(out) -eq- Na+(in) + inorganic phosphate(in).
Catalysis of the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction -  phosphate (cyt) + H+ (cyt) -eq- phosphate (mitochondrion) + H+ (mitochondrion).
Catalysis of the transfer of phosphate (PO4 3-) ions from one side of a membrane to the other, requiring sodium ions.

label.value: secondary active oligopeptide transmembrane transporter activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the transfer of an oligopeptide or oligopeptides from one side of the membrane to the other, up the solute's concentration gradient. The transporter binds the solute and undergoes a series of conformational changes. Transport works equally well in either direction.

label.value: peptide-acetyl-CoA secondary active transmembrane transporter activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the transfer of peptide-acetyl-CoA from one side of a membrane to the other, up its concentration gradient. The transporter binds the solute and undergoes a series of conformational changes. Transport works equally well in either direction and is driven by a chemiosmotic source of energy. Chemiosmotic sources of energy include uniport, symport or antiport.
Catalysis of the reaction -  acetyl-CoA(out) + CoA(in) -eq- acetyl-CoA(in) + CoA(out).
Catalysis of the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction -  cystine(out) + glutamate(in) -eq- cystine(in) + glutamate(out).

label.value: cystine secondary active transmembrane transporter activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the transfer of cystine from one side of a membrane to the other, up its concentration gradient. The transporter binds the solute and undergoes a series of conformational changes. Transport works equally well in either direction and is driven by a chemiosmotic source of energy. Chemiosmotic sources of energy include uniport, symport or antiport.

Catalysis of the high affinity transfer of glutamine from one side of the membrane to the other. In high-affinity transport the transporter is able to bind the solute even if it is only present at very low concentrations.

Catalysis of the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction -  peptide(out) + H+(out) -eq- peptide(in) + H+(in). Catalysis of the transfer of a peptide from one side of a membrane to the other, up its concentration gradient. The transporter binds the solute and undergoes a series of conformational changes. Transport works equally well in either direction and is driven by hydrogen ion movement.

Catalysis of the transfer of oligopeptide from one side of the membrane to the other. In high-affinity transport the transporter is able to bind the solute even if it is only present at very low concentrations. Oligopeptides are molecules that contain a small number (2 to 20) of amino-acid residues connected by peptide linkages.

label.value: zinc efflux active transmembrane transporter activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the transfer of a zinc ion or zinc ions from the inside of the cell to the outside of the cell across a membrane -  Zn2+(out) -eq- Zn2+(in). The activity is driven by proton motive force.
Catalysis of the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction -  siderophore-iron(out) + H+(out) -eq- siderophore-iron(in) + H+(in).

Catalysis of the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction -  siderophore-iron(ferrioxamine)(out) + H+(out) -eq- siderophore-iron(ferrioxamine)(in) + H+(in).
Catalysis of the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction -  ferric enterobactin(out) + H+(out) -eq- ferric enterobactin(in) + H+(in).

label.value: ferric triacetylfusarinine C - proton symporter activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction -  ferric triacetylfusarinine C(out) + H+(out) -eq- ferric triacetylfusarinine C(in) + H+(in).

label.value: sodium-independent organic anion transmembrane transporter activity

definition.value: Catalysis of the transfer of organic anions from one side of a membrane to the other, in a sodium independent manner.

Catalysis of the transfer of thyroid hormones from one side of the membrane to the other. Thyroid hormone are any of the compounds secreted by the thyroid gland, largely thyroxine and triiodothyronine.

Enables the directed movement of methotrexate, 4-amino-10-methylformic acid, into, out of or within a cell, or between cells. Methotrexate is a folic acid analogue and a potent competitive inhibitor of dihydrofolate reductase.
